arts.ttl: Cheltenham Town v Gillingham RECAP: Sam Stubbs header earns point
arts.sum: The Gills opened the scoring in the second minute when Jimmy-Jay Morgan finished past Joe Day after a shot free-kick was played through to him by Jack Nolan. Gillingham: Holtam; Gale, Masterson, Ogie; Hutton, McKenzie, Khumbeni (Rowe 84), Clark; Nolan (Williams 71), Morgan (Dack 60); Nevitt (Hawkins 84).

arts.ttl: Sam Stubbs earns Cheltenham a point against Gillingham
arts.sum: Jimmy Jay-Morgan had opened the scoring for Gills.

arts.ttl: Cheltenham Town prospects earn professional contracts
arts.sum: Tall central defender Walters became the Robins' youngest ever first team player when he started against West Ham United Under-21s in the EFL Trophy on October 18, 2022, aged 16 years and nine days. Cheltenham Town are set to offer professional contracts to youth team prospects Cameron Walters and Harry Tustin.
